 There was jubilation within the All Progressive Congress fold in Pil Gani wards, Langtang North Local Government Area of Plateau State recently as at least, 1,502 members of the Peopleâ€™s Democratic Party defected to the APC. The defectors were received by Zulfa Rimven, the Langtang North LG chairman. Ringa Nanlok, who led the defectors, said that they were satisfied with the council chairman and the administrative style of the Plateau State Governor, Simon Lalong. Rimven, who was accompanied by the Commissioner for Housing, Brian Bintim Dadi, and the APC aspirants for the 2023 elections in the council, assured the defectors of justice and fairness. Urging others who had yet to defect to APC to do so, the council chief, expressed delight that most of the returnees were key members of the PDP. He charged them to use their political weight to ensure victory for the party in the 2023 poll. Vongdul, former PDP Deputy chairman in the ward, assured party faithfuls that their return to APC was to consolidate the achievements of the chairman of the council. 